

We have a noticeable amount of pods that are dropping logs, but not too
many, and we have room to spare.

Vector is bothered when logs get on the 5000/s range, and since kube
limits pods to 100 per node, in theory we could have 500 logs/s per
pod.

Our limit key groups several pod/containers together, so granting 100/s
per limit key should be well inside safe ground.

The real trouble are pods that get into the thousands per second, that
we need to deal with a method different that throttling.
